description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you will be an integral part of a team who are committed to delivering the highest quality clinical outcomes in a supported environment, where you will be valued for your skills and expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a person who wants to work within a motivated and enthusiastic multidisciplinary team and can be a role model, fostering a culture of development and leadership within staff and providing strong clinical leadership and direction within the physiotherapy department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is focused on hand therapy work and the hours can be flexible to meet individual and business needs and can be extended to working in the evening and weekends. We are looking for a committed person with excellent communication skills and a solid clinical background. You will be working with Orthopaedic patients following hand surgeries which ranges from Dupuytren’s contracture to complex tendon reconstructions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be innovative and have excellent communication and organisational skills. You will require an ability to work flexibly, exploring ideas, and adapting practices to deliver more efficient prudent services in line with local and national drivers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring with you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post qualification experience with significant experience in hand surgery rehabilitation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSc Physiotherapy or Specific hand therapy qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work both independently and within a team structure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess, diagnose and provide high quality individualised treatment programmes for patients, being sensitive to patients needs for dignity and privacy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MCSP or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working experience in the UK&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributory pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the Ramsay Academy – genuine opportunities to grow, develop and specialise in your career&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days’ annual leave plus the opportunity to buy/sell more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible shift options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Private Healthcare and Life Assurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free onsite parking and a subsidised staff restaurant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free uniform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to our employee Discount Programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellbeing centre and access to 24/7 employee assistance line for free advice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free DBS checking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long service, Employee recognition and appreciation awards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hospital bonus / employee incentive scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woodland Hospital is proud to have been treating patients in Northamptonshire for 30 years and the hospital continues to focus on delivering high standards of patient care in a friendly and approachable manner. The staff at Woodland Hospital work extremely hard to deliver a personal service to patients, tailored to meet their needs and we receive regular complimentary feedback from our patients. Woodland Hospital has four laminar flow theatres, operating 6 days’ a week, covering a diverse range of elective services including Orthopaedic, General Surgery, Weight Loss Surgery, Cosmetic Surgery, Urology, Gynaecology, ENT and Ophthalmology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ramsay Health Care UK is a well-established global hospital group with over 50 years’ experience. It is well respected within the healthcare industry and is one of the leading providers of independent hospital services in England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We love people with a positive, “can do” attitude who want to make a difference in their work. &quot;Our employees are Ramsay.&quot; The skills and commitment of our employees forms the basis for our success.&lt;/p&gt;
